questions.quote: What are they doin' lettin' you bastards on an airplane? Don't they know that's against FAA regulation?
No buts, Elaine. Or I will strip you of your 'associate' status.  Uh, P.S., the first twenty-four hours are the worst. Better bring a poncho.
What do you mean 'my own words'? Whose words are they gonna be?
Yeah, it's burning my retina. Susan picked that out for you right?
Because he hasn't called me since we got back.. I spilled wine on his 8 by 10 photo of one of his favorite Italian opera stars.
I mean, if he thinks that that baby's breathtaking, then who's not breathtaking?
Tell that to Bobby Colby. All that kid wanted to do was go home. Well he went home alright, with a crater in his colon the size of a cutlet. Had to sit him on a cork the eighteen-hour flight home!
Um, well, he's got a lot of character in his face. Um, he's short. Um, he's stocky.
Well maybe we could go into business together. If you're clean?
Well, I can't argue with that, but the fact remains... I was completely...  Mulva!
